  abstract={Aggregation is a scalable hierachical dispatch regime for using the flexibility of millions of grid-edge devices, such as electric vehicles, heat pumps, and distributed renewables (reactive power controllable). To use the flexibility in a reliable way, a joint chance constraint (JCC) is important to ensure the flexibility delivery with a high probability. However, existing deterministic aggregation is already chanllening. This paper proposes a smart method to incorperate a two-stage JCC into the aggregation process. Rather than formulating the JCC on the original device level, the JCC is formulated on the approximated aggregation level, which makes the overall aggregation have the same order of computational complexity as the deterministic aggregation. }
